VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \bthrow\s*\(
WHEN EXPR PRESENT:~\w+\s*\(\s*\)\s*\{|~\w+\s*\(\s*\)\s*noexcept && MISSING:noexcept|try\s*\{|catch\s*\(|std::terminate
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects exceptions thrown from destructors or deallocation functions.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Exceptions in Destructors: Risk of Unhandled Behavior.
